### ▶ QUESTION A — 14 Marks  *(CO4 + CO5 | Bloom: Apply / Create)*

**"Explain the Model-View-Controller (MVC) architectural pattern with a suitable Java example. In your answer, clearly show:**
**(a) How the Model encapsulates data and notifies the View on change.** *(7 marks)*
**(b) How the Controller mediates between View and Model using event listeners."** *(7 marks)*

#### 🟢 Model Solution — Part (a) : The Model

```java
import java.util.ArrayList;
import java.util.List;

public class Student {
    private String name;
    private double marks;
    private final List<Runnable> listeners = new ArrayList<>();

    public Student(String name, double marks) {
        this.name  = name;
        this.marks = marks;
    }

    public String getName()        { return name; }
    public double getMarks()       { return marks; }
    public String computeGrade()   {
        return marks >= 50 ? "PASS" : "FAIL";   // business rule
    }

    public void setName(String name) {
        this.name = name;
        notifyAllListeners();
    }

    public void setMarks(double marks) {
        if (marks < 0 || marks > 100) throw new IllegalArgumentException();
        this.marks = marks;
        notifyAllListeners();
    }

    public void addListener(Runnable r) { listeners.add(r); }
    private void notifyAllListeners()   { listeners.forEach(Runnable::run); }
}
```

**Explanation (7 marks):**
- **(2 marks)** Model is a **POJO**, encapsulates state with `private` fields.
- **(2 marks)** Business rule `computeGrade()` lives **inside the Model**, not the View.
- **(2 marks)** Mutators validate input and **notify** all subscribed Views.
- **(1 mark)** Add an architecture diagram (see Section 4.1).

#### 🟢 Model Solution — Part (b) : The Controller and View Wiring

```java
import javax.swing.*;
import java.awt.*;
import java.awt.event.*;

public class StudentView extends JFrame {
    JTextField tfName  = new JTextField(10);
    JTextField tfMarks = new JTextField(10);
    JLabel     lbl     = new JLabel("Grade: -");
    JButton    btn     = new JButton("Update");

    public StudentView(Student s) {
        setLayout(new FlowLayout());
        add(new JLabel("Name:"));  add(tfName);
        add(new JLabel("Marks:")); add(tfMarks);
        add(btn); add(lbl);

        s.addListener(() ->
            lbl.setText("Grade: " + s.computeGrade())
        );

        btn.addActionListener(e -> {
            try {
                s.setName(tfName.getText());
                s.setMarks(Double.parseDouble(tfMarks.getText()));
            } catch (Exception ex) {
                JOptionPane.showMessageDialog(this, "Invalid input");
            }
        });

        setSize(300, 200);
        setDefaultCloseOperation(EXIT_ON_CLOSE);
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Student s = new Student("Arjun", 78);
        new StudentView(s).setVisible(true);
    }
}
```

**Explanation (7 marks):**
- **(2 marks)** View subscribes via `s.addListener(...)` — Model drives View updates.
- **(2 marks)** View forwards button click via `ActionListener` — Controller logic embedded.
- **(2 marks)** Validation errors are shown to the user via dialog (graceful failure).
- **(1 mark)** Mention **separation of concerns** explicitly in the conclusion.

