- ✅ MVC = **Model** (data + logic) + **View** (UI) + **Controller** (event mediator).
- ✅ Origin: **Trygve Reenskaug, Xerox PARC, 1979**, Smalltalk.
- ✅ **Model never imports UI libraries** (`javax.swing`, `javafx`, `android.widget`).
- ✅ **View never mutates the Model directly**; it forwards events to the Controller.
- ✅ **Controller is the only class that holds references to both Model and View**.
- ✅ **Observer pattern** is the glue between Model and View (`PropertyChangeListener`, `Runnable`, `LiveData`).
- ✅ The **composition root** (typically `main`) wires the three components once.
- ✅ Advantages to mention: **separation of concerns, loose coupling, high cohesion, reusability, parallel development, multiple views, testability, maintainability**.
- ✅ Disadvantages to mention (for balance): **complexity, learning curve, possible Controller–View coupling**.
- ✅ Variants: **MVP** (Presenter pushes data), **MVVM** (declarative binding), **MVA** (Adapter mediates).
