## 3.7 Walkthrough 7 — KeyAdapter for Keyboard Events

```java
import javax.swing.*;
import java.awt.event.*;

public class KeyEventDemo extends JFrame {

    public KeyEventDemo() {
        setTitle("Press Arrow Keys");
        setSize(300, 200);

        JLabel label = new JLabel("Focus this window and press keys.", SwingConstants.CENTER);
        add(label);

        // KeyAdapter provides empty default methods — override only what you need
        addKeyListener(new KeyAdapter() {
            @Override
            public void keyPressed(KeyEvent e) {
                int code = e.getKeyCode();
                switch (code) {
                    case KeyEvent.VK_UP:    label.setText("UP arrow pressed");    break;
                    case KeyEvent.VK_DOWN:  label.setText("DOWN arrow pressed");  break;
                    case KeyEvent.VK_LEFT:  label.setText("LEFT arrow pressed");  break;
                    case KeyEvent.VK_RIGHT: label.setText("RIGHT arrow pressed"); break;
                }
            }
        });

        setDefaultCloseOperation(EXIT_ON_CLOSE);
        setFocusable(true);   // ensure the JFrame receives key events
        setVisible(true);
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        new KeyEventDemo();
    }
}
```

**The `setFocusable(true)` Pitfall:** A `JFrame` is not focusable by default. If you skip this call, the `KeyListener` will not fire because the window cannot receive keyboard focus.

## 3.8 Summary of Event Listener Registration Methods (Analytical Matrix)

| Component | Method to Register | Listener Interface | Callback Method |
|---|---|---|---|
| `JButton` | `addActionListener(L)` | `ActionListener` | `actionPerformed(ActionEvent e)` |
| `JTextField` | `addActionListener(L)` | `ActionListener` | `actionPerformed(ActionEvent e)` |
| `JCheckBox` | `addItemListener(L)` | `ItemListener` | `itemStateChanged(ItemEvent e)` |
| `JRadioButton` | `addItemListener(L)` | `ItemListener` | `itemStateChanged(ItemEvent e)` |
| `JComboBox` | `addActionListener(L)` | `ActionListener` | `actionPerformed(ActionEvent e)` |
| `JList` | `addListSelectionListener(L)` | `ListSelectionListener` | `valueChanged(ListSelectionEvent e)` |
| `JTable` | `addListSelectionListener(L)` (on selection model) | `ListSelectionListener` | `valueChanged(ListSelectionEvent e)` |
| `JSlider` | `addChangeListener(L)` | `ChangeListener` | `stateChanged(ChangeEvent e)` |
| `JMenuItem` | `addActionListener(L)` | `ActionListener` | `actionPerformed(ActionEvent e)` |
| Any Component | `addKeyListener(L)` | `KeyListener` | `keyTyped/Pressed/Released(KeyEvent e)` |
| Any Component | `addMouseListener(L)` | `MouseListener` | `mouseClicked/Pressed/... (MouseEvent e)` |
| `JFrame` | `addWindowListener(L)` | `WindowListener` | `windowClosing/Opened/... (WindowEvent e)` |
