## SECTION 5 — KTU 2024 Scheme Examination Question Bank & Topic Recap

### 5.1 Part A Questions (3 Marks Each)

**Q1. [KTU University Exam – Dec 2023]**
*What is the Delegation Event Model in Java? List its key participants.*

**Model Answer (3 marks):**
The **Delegation Event Model** is the mechanism used by Java AWT and Swing to handle user interactions. In this model, a component (called the **event source**) does not handle events itself; instead, it **delegates** the task to one or more registered objects (called **event listeners**). The three key participants are:
1. **Event Source** — the GUI component generating the event (e.g., `JButton`).
2. **Event Object** — a subclass of `java.util.EventObject` describing the event (e.g., `ActionEvent`).
3. **Event Listener** — an object implementing a listener interface (e.g., `ActionListener`) whose callback method is invoked when the event occurs.

*(+0.5 for mentioning registration via `addXxxListener`.)*

**Q2. [KTU University Exam – June 2024]**
*Differentiate between an event listener and an event adapter. Give one example of each.*

**Model Answer (3 marks):**
An **event listener** is an *interface* (e.g., `MouseListener`) that declares the callback methods an event-handling class must implement. An **event adapter** is a *concrete class* (e.g., `MouseAdapter`) that provides empty default implementations of all methods in a listener interface, so subclasses can override only the methods they need. Adapters are used to avoid writing empty method bodies. **Example:** `WindowListener` (interface) vs. `WindowAdapter` (class).

