### 5.3 Topic Recap & Important Things to Remember

- **Delegation Event Model** has three pillars: **Source**, **Event**, **Listener**. Memorize this trio.
- Registration is always done via `component.addXxxListener(handlerObject)`.
- The handler must implement a listener interface **or extend an adapter class**.
- **`ActionListener`** has a single method `actionPerformed(ActionEvent e)` — most common in exams.
- **`MouseListener`** has 5 methods; use `MouseAdapter` to avoid writing empty bodies.
- **`KeyListener`** has 3 methods; `KeyEvent.VK_ENTER`, `VK_ESCAPE` etc. are `int` constants from `getKeyCode()`.
- **`WindowListener`** has 7 methods; `WindowAdapter` is the typical exam pick.
- Use `e.getSource()` when one handler services multiple components.
- Use `e.getActionCommand()` to differentiate buttons sharing a single handler (works for `JButton`, `JMenuItem`).
- For Swing-specific events (e.g., `ChangeEvent` from `JSlider`), import from `javax.swing.event`; for AWT events, `java.awt.event`.
- Always override `windowClosing` and call `System.exit(0)` to gracefully terminate.
- Inner classes and anonymous classes are the cleanest way to write one-off listeners for KTU practical exams.

